OL,3,CCouncillor who oversaw bin services
OL,4,Cduring strikes resigns from Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,FHe said the party "has become more
OL,8,Fmanagerial, centralised, and
OL,9,Fconstrained in its tolerance of
OL,10,Finternal difference, both locally and
OL,11,Fnationally. For these reasons, I can
OL,12,Fno longer remain a member in good
OL,13,Fconscience."
OL,15,F"I am also deeply concerned by the
OL,16,Fdirection of Labour's immigration
OL,17,Fpolicy, which appears increasingly
OL,18,Fshaped by political expediency rather
OL,19,Fthan principle or long-term vision.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
