PN,37306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781291475
OL,3,CCouncillor who oversaw bin services
OL,4,Cduring strikes resigns from Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,FHe wrote: "In my view, the current
OL,8,Flocal leadership lacks the experience,
OL,9,Fjudgement, and political competence
OL,10,Frequired to effectively manage a group
OL,11,Fin a city as complex and demanding as
OL,12,FBirmingham.
OL,14,F"My views no longer fit comfortably
OL,15,Fwithin a Labour Party. Ultimately, the
OL,16,FLabour Party has left me, not the
OL,17,Fother way around.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781291475
OL,3,CCouncillor who oversaw bin services
OL,4,Cduring strikes resigns from Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,F"I will continue to work to represent
OL,8,Fthe people of Bromford and Hodge Hill
OL,9,Fwith my ward colleague Cllr Diane
OL,10,FDonaldson and to stand up for the
OL,11,Fcommunities and values that first led
OL,12,Fme into public service."
OL,14,FA spokesperson for the Birmingham
OL,15,FLabour Group told ITV News Central:
OL,16,F"Since the local elections, Cllr
OL,17,FMahmood has repeatedly sought to
OL,18,Fundermine the Labour Group and its new
OL,19,Fleadership.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781291475
OL,3,CCouncillor who oversaw bin services
OL,4,Cduring strikes resigns from Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,F"He had the opportunity to stand for
OL,8,FGroup Leader and make his case to
OL,9,Fcolleagues, but chose not to. Labour
OL,10,Fmembers were elected to work as a team
OL,11,Ffor Birmingham residents and Cllr
OL,12,FMahmood has decided barely a month
OL,13,Fafter being elected on a Labour ticket
OL,14,Fhe no longer wants to be part of that
OL,15,Fteam.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,374,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1781291475
OL,3,CCouncillor who oversaw bin services
OL,4,Cduring strikes resigns from Labour
OL,5,CParty
OL,7,F"Our priority will always be
OL,8,FBirmingham residents. The Labour Group
OL,9,Fwill continue working as a united
OL,10,Fteam, providing a strong and
OL,11,Fconstructive opposition and serving
OL,12,Four communities across the city."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/9
